n Britain."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Gifford was born about 1260, in Yester, East Lothian, Scotland, United Kingdom. He had at least 2 sons with William Gifford. He died after 15 June 1310, in his hometown."},"et":{"about 1260–after 15 June 1310":"umbes 1260–pärast 15. juunit 1310","1279–Female":"1279–Surnud","1278–1345":"1278–1345","1297–Male":"1297–Surnud","1260–1310":"1260–1310","about 1260":"umbes 1260","1345":"1345","1279":"1279","1278":"1278","1310":"1310","1297":"1297","after 15 June 1310":"pärast 15. juunit 1310","about 1297":"umbes 1297","1260":"1260","Gifford, East Lothian, Scotland":"Yester, East Lothian, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Peeblesshire, Scotland","Yester, East Lothian, Scotland":"Yester, Haddingtonshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1260–after 15 June 1310":"noin 1260–15. kesäkuuta 1310 jälkeen","1279–Female":"1279–Kuollut","1278–1345":"1278–1345","1297–Male":"1297–Kuollut","1260–1310":"1260–1310","about 1260":"noin 1260","1345":"1345","1279":"1279","1278":"1278","1310":"1310","1297":"1297","after 15 June 1310":"15. kesäkuuta 1310 jälkeen","about 1297":"noin 1297","1260":"1260","Gifford, East Lothian, Scotland":"Yester, East Lothian, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunt